nodes.body: The equivalence I really want is `LocallyConstant X (Fin 2) ≃ Clopens X` (see #10391), but I can't write that in either file, because neither imports the other, and I didn't want to change the imports in these files.
I don't see why you couldn't change the imports of `LocallyConstant/Basic.lean` to import `Sets/Closeds.lean` instead, as it didn't seem to cause any issues on my end

Yeah it doesn't cause any issues, but I'm always wary of changing the import structure in these basic files. Maybe @semorrison can comment on whether it's ok to change the imports of `LocallyConstant/Basic.lean`?
Maybe the least harmful option is to create a new, tiny file `LocallyConstant/Clopens.lean` which imports `LocallyConstant.Basic` and `Sets.Closed`, with only this equivalence?
That would be an alternative solution, yeah, if adding the import really doesn't work
